  <h1>
   window_get_fullscreen
  </h1>
  This function returns whether the game window is in fullscreen mode (
  <span>
   true
  </span>
  ) or not (
  <span>
   false
  </span>
  ).
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">window_get_fullscreen();
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Boolean
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if window_get_fullscreen()
{
    draw_text(32, 32, "Fullscreen is ON");
}
else
{
    draw_text(32, 32, "Fullscreen is OFF");
}
</code></pre>
  The above code will check to see if the window is in full screen mode or not and draw a text message depending on the returned value.
 </body>
